history.content:
Enrollment priorities for CS classes are explained here http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Policies/enrollment.shtml.  EECS students are only guaranteed space in lower division cs classes until the final phase 2 undergraduate appointment date which for Fall15 was August 5th or 6th.  It is also absolutely true that if there is no space in the lab/dis section you chose, we can't enroll you into the class.

The good news is that 61A is being expanded to be able to accommodate up to 1400 students and many new dis/lab sections will be created sometime this week.  If you are not enrolled by Thursday, feel free to reach out directly to me (either by e-mail at sasson@berkeley.edu or by stopping by my office at 379 Soda) and I can try to help if you are willing to identify yourself.

children.subject: you will remain on the waitlist for the full section

If the dis/lab sections I chose are full but more sections at the same time/date are added, will I be automatically put into the new sections that have space, or will I remain on the waitlist of a full section?

history.content:
Incoming Freshman EECS Major. I temporarily dropped it on Telebears in order to get the seminar I wanted without going over the units limit. I was told during CalSO that we're guaranteed a spot, so I didn't worry about it. When I added CS61A back on I got put on the waitlist (position 707). What should I do now?

Also, is choosing a full Lab/Discussion section going to prevent me from getting off a waitlist?
